A startup item script to automatically start up MongoDB on system bootup
for Mac OS X.

By default the script assumes that MongoDB is installed in /usr/local/mongodb
and that the dbpath /var/db/mongodb exists. You may change this in the script
by yourself.

Author: Ren√© Sprotte (@renspr on Twitter)

Installation
============

1.) Copy the folder mongodb to /Library/StartupItems
2.) Restart your Mac
